  "content": `
<h2>Crisis as Brand Test</h2>

<p>Political campaigns inevitably face crises—scandals, gaffes, attacks, or unexpected events that threaten candidate reputation and electoral prospects. Crisis response significantly affects outcomes; mishandled crises destroy campaigns while effectively managed crises can demonstrate resilience. Brand crisis management prepares for inevitable challenges.</p>

<p>Crisis management requires rapid response capability; clear decision-making processes; and pre-prepared frameworks enabling quick action under pressure. Preparation essential for effective response.</p>

<h2>Crisis Preparation</h2>

<p>Risk assessment identifying potential vulnerabilities. Personal history; policy positions; and opposition research. Vulnerability mapping.</p>

<p>Response team and protocol establishment. Decision makers; spokespersons; and communication channels. Structure preparation.</p>

<p>Scenario planning for likely crises. Response templates; message frameworks; and action checklists. Preparatory planning.</p>

<p>Monitoring systems for early warning. Media monitoring; social listening; and intelligence networks. Early detection.</p>

<h2>Crisis Response</h2>

<p>Rapid response minimizing damage. Speed; accuracy; and control. Timeliness.</p>

<p>Message discipline maintaining consistency. Core message; unified voice; and controlled communication. Coherence.</p>

<p>Transparency and accountability when appropriate. Acknowledgment; responsibility; and corrective action. Integrity.</p>

<p>Counter-attack when justified. Fact correction; opponent exposure; and narrative reframing. Defense.</p>

<h2>Recovery and Rehabilitation</h2>

<p>Reputation rebuilding post-crisis. Positive messaging; third-party validation; and time. Recovery.</p>

<p>Learning integration preventing recurrence. Analysis; process improvement; and preparation updating. Learning.</p>

<p>Luna Graphics provides crisis management support for political campaigns, helping protect brand integrity under pressure. Contact our crisis team before you need us.</p>
  `,
