  "content": `
<h2>Timing as Campaign Strategy</h2>

<p>Print production timing significantly affects campaign effectiveness—too early and materials become outdated or damaged; too late and opportunities missed; poorly coordinated and distribution bottlenecks occur. Strategic printing timeline aligns production with campaign phases, voter attention patterns, and logistical requirements.</p>

<p>2027 election timeline requires backward planning from polling day—early materials for foundation building; peak production for intense campaigning; and final push for get-out-the-vote.</p>

<h2>Phase-Based Production</h2>

<p>Pre-campaign foundation (12+ months before). Brand development; template creation; and early visibility. Foundation.</p>

<p>Early campaign (6-12 months). Awareness building; initial materials; and organizational presence. Introduction.</p>

<p>Active campaign (3-6 months). Intense production; mass distribution; and saturation. Intensification.</p>

<p>Peak campaign (1-3 months). Maximum volume; rapid response; and full deployment. Peak.</p>

<p>Get-out-the-vote (final month). Reminder materials; mobilization tools; and turnout focus. Final push.</p>

<h2>Logistical Coordination</h2>

<p>Production scheduling with vendors. Capacity booking; phased production; and quality control. Supply management.</p>

<p>Inventory management and warehousing. Storage; distribution hubs; and tracking. Logistics.</p>

<p>Distribution timing for maximum impact. Deployment waves; regional coordination; and event alignment. Distribution.</p>

<p>Emergency and contingency capacity. Rush production; backup vendors; and crisis response. Flexibility.</p>

<p>Luna Graphics provides timeline planning and production management for 2027 election printing. We ensure materials arrive at right time, right place, right quality. Contact our election timeline team.</p>
  `,
