<p>Site visits provide irreplaceable insight. Observe facility organization—clean, well-maintained environments suggest operational discipline. Machine condition indicates maintenance standards and investment commitment. Staff interaction reveals technical knowledge and professionalism. Material storage and handling practices affect output quality. While not always feasible, site visits for initial qualification or large project kickoff significantly reduce selection risk.</p>

