    "excerpt": "Extend the life of CNC cut products with proper maintenance. Learn care procedures, cleaning methods, and preservation strategies for various materials and applications.",
    "content": `
<h2>Maintaining CNC Cut Product Investment</h2>

<p>CNC cut products represent investment in quality materials and precision manufacturing. Appropriate maintenance protects this investment, extending product life and maintaining appearance. Maintenance requirements vary dramatically by material, environment, and use intensity—understanding specific needs ensures effective care without unnecessary effort or damage from inappropriate methods.</p>

<p>This guide provides maintenance guidance across material categories, addressing cleaning, protection, repair, and restoration. Proper maintenance not only extends life but often enhances appearance as materials develop patina and character.</p>

<h2>Wood and Wood Composite Maintenance</h2>

<p><strong>Regular Cleaning:</strong> Dust with soft, dry cloth; damp cloth for stubborn dirt (immediately dried); avoid excessive moisture; and never use harsh chemicals or abrasives on finished surfaces.</p>

<p><strong>Moisture Management:</strong> Wood's primary enemy. Wipe spills immediately; use coasters under drinks; maintain consistent indoor humidity (40-60%); and avoid placement near heat sources or direct sunlight causing drying and cracking.</p>

<p><strong>Surface Protection:</strong> Use felt pads under objects preventing scratches; avoid dragging items across surfaces; and use placemats or desk pads for writing/working surfaces.</p>

<p><strong>Refinishing Schedule:</strong> Oiled finishes: Reapply every 6-12 months or when wood appears dry. Varnished/lacquered finishes: Inspect annually for wear; touch up as needed; full refinish every 5-10 years depending on wear. Wax finishes: Re wax every 3-6 months.</p>

${createTable(
  ['Wood Type/Finish', 'Cleaning Method', 'Protection', 'Refinishing Frequency'],
  [
  ['Oiled wood', 'Damp cloth, dry immediately', 'Coasters, pads', '6-12 months'],
  ['Varnished wood', 'Mild soap and water', 'Avoid heat/scratch', '5-10 years'],
  ['Painted MDF', 'Damp cloth, mild cleaner', 'Avoid moisture on edges', 'Touch up as needed'],
  ['Laminate', 'All-purpose cleaner', 'Heat protection', 'Replace when worn'],
  ['Outdoor wood', 'Brush, mild detergent', 'Water repellent', 'Annually']
  ]
)}

<h2>Metal Maintenance</h2>

<p><strong>Aluminum (Anodized):</strong> Clean with mild soap and water; avoid abrasive cleaners damaging anodized layer; and restore shine with aluminum polish if desired.</p>

<p><strong>Stainless Steel:</strong> Clean with stainless steel cleaner or mild detergent; wipe with grain direction; and remove fingerprints with glass cleaner or specialized stainless cleaner.</p>

<p><strong>Steel (Painted/Powder Coated):</strong> Wash with mild detergent; touch up chips promptly preventing rust; and avoid abrasive cleaning.</p>

<p><strong>Brass/Bronze:</strong> Polish with appropriate metal polish if shiny finish desired; or allow natural patina development; and protect lacquered finishes from abrasion.</p>

<p><strong>Corten Steel:</strong> No maintenance required; natural weathering process; and manage run-off staining adjacent materials.</p>

<h2>Plastic and Acrylic Maintenance</h2>

<p><strong>Acrylic:</strong> Clean with mild soap and water or acrylic cleaner; use soft cloth (microfiber) avoiding scratches; remove scratches with acrylic polish; and avoid ammonia-based cleaners (Windex) causing crazing.</p>

<p><strong>PVC and Plastics:</strong> Soap and water cleaning; avoid solvents; and check for UV degradation (yellowing, brittleness) in outdoor applications.</p>

<p><strong>Polycarbonate:</strong> Similar to acrylic but more scratch-resistant; mild cleaners safe; and avoid abrasives.</p>

<h2>Surface-Specific Care</h2>

<p><strong>Painted Surfaces:</strong> Gentle cleaning with mild soap; immediate attention to chips preventing moisture ingress; touch-up paint matching original; and avoid waxing or polishing painted surfaces.</p>

<p><strong>Natural Stone/Solid Surface:</strong> pH-neutral cleaners; avoid acidic or abrasive cleaners; blot spills immediately (especially acidic substances); and periodic resealing if recommended by manufacturer.</p>

<p><strong>Laminate Surfaces:</strong> General purpose cleaners; avoid excessive water on edges; heat protection; and avoid cutting directly on surface.</p>

<h2>Environmental Protection</h2>

<p><strong>UV Protection:</strong> Minimize direct sunlight exposure; use window treatments (blinds, UV film); and rotate objects periodically ensuring even exposure.</p>

<p><strong>Climate Control:</strong> Maintain stable temperature and humidity; avoid placement near HVAC vents, fireplaces, or exterior doors; and use humidifiers/dehumidifiers as needed.</p>

<p><strong>Pest Prevention:</strong> Regular inspection for wood-boring insects; maintain cleanliness preventing pest attraction; and professional treatment if infestation suspected.</p>

<h2>Repair and Restoration</h2>

<p><strong>Minor Damage:</strong> Small scratches in wood: Touch-up markers or wax sticks. Dents: Steam treatment for wood; replacement for severe damage. Chips: Fill and refinish matching surrounding area.</p>

<p><strong>Professional Restoration:</strong> Significant damage requires professional assessment. Structural repairs; refinishing; and component replacement.</p>

<p><strong>Spare Parts:</strong> Maintain records of CNC cut products enabling spare part production from original files. Contact manufacturer for replacement components.</p>

<h2>Inspection Schedules</h2>

<p><strong>Monthly:</strong> Visual inspection for damage, loose hardware, or wear; cleaning; and tightening of any loose fasteners.</p>

<p><strong>Annually:</strong> Comprehensive inspection; deep cleaning; finish condition assessment; hardware lubrication; and refinishing touch-up as needed.</p>

<p><strong>As Needed:</strong> Immediate attention to damage, spills, or environmental exposure (water, extreme temperature).</p>

<p>Luna Graphics provides maintenance guidance specific to products we manufacture. Our customer service team advises on care procedures, refinishing options, and spare part availability. Contact us for maintenance support ensuring your CNC cut products provide lasting value.</p>
    `,
